      <div dir="ltr">Hi Gilles,
        <div><br>
        </div>
        <div>Thank you a lot, it works now.</div>
        <div><br>
        </div>
        <div>Just one minor thing I have seen now. If I use some
          communicator size which does not exist in the configuration
          file, it will still use the configuration file. For example,
          if I use the previous config file with mpirun -n 4 it will use
          the config for the comm size 5 (the first one). The same
          happens if n is less than 16. If n &gt; 16 it will use the
          config for the communicator size 16 (the second one). I am
          writing this just in case it is not expected behaviour.</div>
        <div><br>
        </div>
        <div>Thanks again.</div>
        <div><br>
        </div>
        <div>Best regards,</div>
        <div>Khalid</div>
